2. Class envy is an interesting topic.  After thinking about it a bit, I've decided that my problem is not class envy.  I come from a very wealthy background, and I don't recall the money making me any happier than I am now.<br>
3. I do think some professions are underpaid, yes.  "Teacher" comes immediately to mind.  These men and women spend day in and day out trying to expand the minds and opportunities of children for so little pay that many of them are on food stamps.  (Especially those in the public school system.)  Yet they continue to do it.  I think they deserve  more money -- if teaching paid more, we wouldn't have the dearth of teachers we do now.  Overworked and underpaid, but I guess there must be some reason they do it....<br>
